      "source": "---\n\n# Module 3: Agentic AI with Strands (30 min)\n\n> **Concept**: An agent is an LLM with tools. **Strands Agents SDK** uses a model-driven approach — you give the LLM tools (Python functions with `@tool`) and it decides when to call them. The agent loops until it has enough information to answer.\n> \n> **What we solve**: The assistant can now search KB, query graph, classify risk, record decisions, AND capture decisions from email threads — all in natural conversation."
    },
