d LLE Context Worth Noting\n\nThe **GENERATOR** sub-category was added to LLE alongside **AHU** as of **DEC-004 (2024-07-01)** per a FY2024 GAAP reclassification — increasing LLE transaction volume by **~15%**. This higher volume made the false positive rate from the 60-day threshold even more impactful, reinforcing the case for the 90-day change.\n\n---\n\n### 🧠 Summary\n\n- **What tracks it:** `po_aging_not_invoiced` in `veritas_po_metrics`, filtering `days_since_receipt > 90` and `invoice_status = PENDING`\n- **Why 90 and not 60:** A data-driven audit finding (40% false positives) led Sarah Chen to approve the change in Oct 2024, reducing noise by 35% and better aligning with actual LLE procurement cycles\n\nWould you like me to run a current risk classification on open aged POs, or check GRC controls related to PO aging compliance?\n\n"
